# .prettierignore Template

## Purpose

Exclude files from Prettier formatting. Prevents formatting of generated code, dependencies, and files where formatting would be destructive.

## Official Documentation

- [Prettier - Ignoring Code](https://prettier.io/docs/en/ignore) - Official guide
- [CLI File Patterns](https://prettier.io/docs/en/cli#file-patterns) - Pattern matching

## When to Use

- ✅ Projects using Prettier for code formatting
- ✅ Monorepos with mixed content types
- ✅ Projects with generated code

## When NOT to Use

- ❌ Projects not using Prettier
- ❌ Single-file projects (use inline comments instead)

## Required Marker Files

- `package.json` with Prettier dependency
- `.prettierrc*` or `prettier.config.js` (optional but common)

## Trade-offs & Alternatives

| Alternative | When to Use Instead |
|-------------|---------------------|
| `<!-- prettier-ignore -->` | Single block in markdown/HTML |
| `// prettier-ignore` | Single statement in code |
| `"prettier": {"ignore": [...]}` | package.json inline config |

## Template

```gitignore
# =============================================================================
# .prettierignore - <PROJECT_NAME>
# =============================================================================

# === Build Output ===
dist/
build/
out/
.next/
.nuxt/
.output/

# === Dependencies ===
node_modules/
vendor/

# === Generated Files ===
*.min.js
*.min.css
*.bundle.js
*.generated.*

# === Lock Files ===
# These have specific formatting
package-lock.json
yarn.lock
pnpm-lock.yaml

# === Type Declarations ===
*.d.ts

# === Coverage & Reports ===
coverage/
.nyc_output/

# === Markdown with Intentional Formatting ===
# Uncomment if you have markdown that shouldn't be touched
# CHANGELOG.md

# === Auto-Generated Docs ===
docs/api/
docs/generated/

# === Third-Party / Vendored ===
public/vendor/
static/lib/

# <PROJECT_SPECIFIC_IGNORES>
```

