## Inline Ignore Comments

For single exceptions within formatted code:

### JavaScript/TypeScript
```javascript
// prettier-ignore
const matrix = [
  1, 0, 0,
  0, 1, 0,
  0, 0, 1,
];
```

### HTML
```html
<!-- prettier-ignore -->
<pre>
  Preformatted    text
</pre>
```

### Markdown
```markdown
<!-- prettier-ignore -->
| Column 1 | Column 2 |
|----------|----------|
| Special  | Format   |
```

### CSS
```css
/* prettier-ignore */
.selector {
  specific: formatting;
}
```

### JSX
```jsx
{/* prettier-ignore */}
<div className="keep    spaces">
  Content
</div>
```

## Ignore Ranges

```javascript
// prettier-ignore-start
const a = 1;
const b = 2;
const c = 3;
// prettier-ignore-end
```

## Validation Commands

```bash
# Check what files Prettier will format
npx prettier --list-different .

# Check specific file
npx prettier --check path/to/file.js

# See which files would be formatted
npx prettier --write --list-different . 2>/dev/null

# Debug ignore patterns
npx prettier --debug-check path/to/file.js
```

## Syncing with .eslintignore

Often you want the same files ignored by both tools:

```bash
# Common approach: start with eslintignore, add prettier-specific
cat .eslintignore > .prettierignore
echo "" >> .prettierignore
echo "# Prettier-specific" >> .prettierignore
echo "package-lock.json" >> .prettierignore
```

## Integration Notes

- `.prettierignore` uses gitignore syntax
- Patterns are relative to `.prettierignore` location
- `node_modules/` is ignored by default
- Files in `.gitignore` can optionally be ignored via `--ignore-unknown`
- Consider VS Code settings to respect ignore on format-on-save

### VS Code Settings
```json
{
  "editor.formatOnSave": true,
  "prettier.ignorePath": ".prettierignore"
}
```

## Common Pitfalls

❌ **Don't ignore:**
- Source code that should be formatted
- Config files (unless team agrees)

✅ **Do ignore:**
- Generated files (will be overwritten anyway)
- Lock files (have specific format)
- Minified files (destroys optimization)
- Third-party vendor code (not your responsibility)
